Class Char2DoubleMaps.Singleton

java.lang.Object

Direct Known Subclasses:
Char2DoubleSortedMaps.Singleton
Enclosing class:
Char2DoubleMaps
public static class Char2DoubleMaps.Singleton extends Char2DoubleFunctions.Singleton implements Char2DoubleMap, Serializable, Cloneable
An immutable class representing a type-specific singleton map.

This class may be useful to implement your own in case you subclass a type-specific map.

    • char2DoubleEntrySet

      public ObjectSet<Char2DoubleMap.Entry> char2DoubleEntrySet()
      Description copied from interface: Char2DoubleMap
      Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

      This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Map.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

      Specified by:
      char2DoubleEntrySet in interface Char2DoubleMap
      Returns:
      a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.
